description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a full time post of Fy2 in General Surgery which include colorectal, breast and general services. The successful candidate will be expected to commence as soon as possible and this will be a permanent post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will gain experience of working in a busy DGH as well as experience of laparoscopic colorectal, vascular, general and breast surgery. The successful candidate will also participate in the on call rota along with the current trainees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will require full registration with the General Medical Council. The post-holder will be encouraged to develop clinical, managerial and educational skills within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals NHS Trust has an ongoing commitment to first class service delivery and innovative long-term initiatives and has now been awarded Associate University Hospital Teaching Status with University College London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is situated in the South East of England, close to London and the M25.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Mr Wayne Chicken, Clinical Lead for General Surgery &amp; Urology on 01268 524900 ext. 8498 or Mark Passey, Service Unit Manager on ext. 8543.&lt;/p&gt;
